    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Office of the Jewish Messenger</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>119 West Houston Street</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>Aug. 7. 1864</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Esteemed Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><persName>M. Crehange</persName> a<lb/> member of the central
                committee of the<lb/> “Universal Israelite Alliance” is<lb/> in <placeName>New
                    York</placeName> on a brief visit and has<lb/> requested me to furnish him
                such<lb/> statistical matter, reports, &amp;c. relative<lb/> to the Israelites of
                the <placeName>United States</placeName><lb/> as might prove of interest &amp; value
                to<lb/> the archives of the Alliance.<lb/> May I ask that you will kindly<lb/>
                forward to me (this week, if possible,<lb/> as <persName>Mr Crehange</persName>
                leaves about the <date>17th</date>.)<lb/> any documents of this character
                con<lb/>cerning the Israelites of <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>,<lb/> such as
                reports of the Education Society,<lb/> Foster Home, &amp;c.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is greatly to be regretted that<lb/> a session of the Board of
                Delegates<lb/> is again rendered impracticable this<lb/> summer, by the presence of
                war and<lb/> the difficulty of communicating<lb/> with members of the Board. I<lb/>
                presume all that the committee<lb/> can do is to continue acting, should occasion
                demand it, and do all<lb/> in its power for the promotion of<lb/> the objects of the
                Board. I had<lb/> expected the receipt of a document<lb/> you proposed drafting
                &amp; forwarding<lb/> to the <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> members for signature<lb/>
                so that congregations throughout the<lb/> Union may be reminded of the<lb/> duty of
                sending delegates; but I<lb/> suppose you considered it inopportune<lb/> and
                therefore delayed its preparation.<lb/> Any request you have to make of<lb/> me with
                reference to the Board<lb/> will be readily &amp; cheerfully acted</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>upon.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If I mistake not, I am<lb/> still indebted to you in the sum<lb/> of
                $6. for the unbound Bible<lb/> sent me last <date>May</date>. Please<lb/> find it
                enclosed.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">How do you progress with <persName>Miss<lb/> Aguilar's</persName>
                works; will not the<lb/> first volume soon appear?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Trusting you will kindly assist<lb/> me in procuring the
                desired<lb/> documents for the “Alliance”,<lb/> I am, dear sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Very Truly Yours,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">M J Isaacs</persName>.</p>
        </body>
